</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="83.[151,1438,152,1454]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,456,1118,1144]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
Specimens of this species were identified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Skov, F." box="[1052,1207,1118,1144]" journalOrPublisher="University of Aarhus, Denmark" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" pagination="1 - 191" refId="ref124280" refString="Skov, F. (1989) Hyper Taxonomy-a new tool for revisional work and a revision of Geonoma (Palmae) in Ecuador. Ph. D. Thesis, University of Aarhus, Denmark, pp. 1 - 191." title="Hyper Taxonomy-a new tool for revisional work and a revision of Geonoma (Palmae) in Ecuador" type="book chapter" year="1989">Skov (1989)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martius" authorityYear="1823" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pauciflora">
<emphasis box="[1266,1380,1118,1144]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Geonoma</emphasis>
aff. 
<emphasis box="[151,276,1157,1183]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">pauciflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and were considered by 
<bibRefCitation author="Borchsenius F. &amp; Borgtoft Pedersen, H. &amp; Balslev, H" box="[586,891,1157,1184]" journalOrPublisher="AAU Report 37" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" pagination="1 - 217" refId="ref120953" refString="Borchsenius F., Borgtoft Pedersen, H. &amp; Balslev, H .. (1998) Manual of the palms of Ecuador. AAU Report 37: 1 - 217." title="Manual of the palms of Ecuador" type="book chapter" year="1998">
Borchsenius 
<emphasis box="[742,803,1157,1184]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">et al.</emphasis>
(1998)
</bibRefCitation>
as a western Andean form of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trail" authorityYear="1876" box="[1257,1428,1157,1183]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leptospadix">
<emphasis box="[1257,1428,1157,1183]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">G. leptospadix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Henderson, Borchsenius &amp; Balslev" authorityYear="2008" box="[151,351,1196,1222]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanata">
<emphasis box="[151,351,1196,1222]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Geonoma lanata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not closely related to either species, and belongs to a group of 12 species, the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Henderson, Borchsenius &amp; Balslev" authorityYear="2008" box="[1326,1436,1196,1222]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanata">
<emphasis box="[1326,1436,1196,1222]" italics="true" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">G. lanata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade. It differs from these in its alternately arranged flower pits and bumpy fruits with numerous, subepidermal, tangential, short fibers present, these coming to a point at fruit apices.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="83.[151,1438,152,1454]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,506,1312,1338]" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Subspecific variation:—</emphasis>
Only one trait (stem branching) varies in this species. There is geographic disjunction but this may be an artifact of insufficient collecting. Most specimens are from the northern part of the range, and only four from the southern part–too few to test for differences. 
<bibRefCitation author="Galeano, G. &amp; R. Bernal" box="[1125,1436,1389,1415]" journalOrPublisher="Universidad Nacional de Colombia, Bogota" pageId="83" pageNumber="84" pagination="1 - 688" refId="ref122268" refString="Galeano, G. &amp; R. Bernal. (2010) Palmas de Colombia - Guia de Campo. Universidad Nacional de Colombia, Bogota. pp. 1 - 688." title="Palmas de Colombia - Guia de Campo" type="book chapter" year="2010">Galeano &amp; Bernal (2010)</bibRefCitation>
report that this species also occurs in southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[751,870,1428,1454]" name="Colombia" pageId="83" pageNumber="84">Colombia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
